  <qti-response-declaration identifier="RESPONSE" cardinality="single" base-type="identifier">
    <qti-correct-response>
      <qti-value>B</qti-value>
    </qti-correct-response>
  </qti-response-declaration>
  <qti-outcome-declaration identifier="SCORE" cardinality="single" base-type="float"/>
  <qti-outcome-declaration identifier="FEEDBACK" cardinality="single" base-type="identifier"/>
  <qti-item-body>
    <qti-choice-interaction max-choices="1" response-identifier="RESPONSE">
      <qti-prompt data-catalog-idref="tts_prompt">
        <p>According to the lesson, plot is best understood as —</p>
      </qti-prompt>
      <qti-simple-choice fixed="true" identifier="A">
        <div data-catalog-idref="tts_choice_A">
          <p>the point of the story all by itself</p>
        </div>
        <qti-feedback-block identifier="feedback_A" outcome-identifier="FEEDBACK" show-hide="show">
          <qti-content-body>
            <div class="tb-feedback-incorrect" data-catalog-idref="feedback_A">
              <p>That's the instinct the lesson warns against — chasing "and then what happens?" as if the events were the whole point.</p>
            </div>
          </qti-content-body>
        </qti-feedback-block>
      </qti-simple-choice>
      <qti-simple-choice fixed="true" identifier="B">
        <div data-catalog-idref="tts_choice_B">
          <p>the path the author uses to deliver meaning</p>
        </div>
        <qti-feedback-block identifier="feedback_B" outcome-identifier="FEEDBACK" show-hide="show">
          <qti-content-body>
            <div class="tb-feedback-correct" data-catalog-idref="feedback_B">
              <p>Correct! Plot is not the point itself but the path through which the author delivers meaning.</p>
            </div>
          </qti-content-body>
        </qti-feedback-block>
      </qti-simple-choice>
      <qti-simple-choice fixed="true" identifier="C">
        <div data-catalog-idref="tts_choice_C">
          <p>a random list of events</p>
        </div>
        <qti-feedback-block identifier="feedback_C" outcome-identifier="FEEDBACK" show-hide="show">
          <qti-content-body>
            <div class="tb-feedback-incorrect" data-catalog-idref="feedback_C">
              <p>A list of stuff that happened in order isn't a story yet — plot is that list given shape by conflict.</p>
            </div>
          </qti-content-body>
        </qti-feedback-block>
      </qti-simple-choice>
      <qti-simple-choice fixed="true" identifier="D">
        <div data-catalog-idref="tts_choice_D">
          <p>only the climax of the story</p>
        </div>
        <qti-feedback-block identifier="feedback_D" outcome-identifier="FEEDBACK" show-hide="show">
          <qti-content-body>
            <div class="tb-feedback-incorrect" data-catalog-idref="feedback_D">
              <p>The climax is one of five stages — plot is the whole shape, not a single peak.</p>
            </div>
          </qti-content-body>
        </qti-feedback-block>
      </qti-simple-choice>
    </qti-choice-interaction>
  </qti-item-body>
